<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7434> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7434" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Listed in the consilium in the SC de agro Pergameno; see now Sherk, RDGE no. 12, 63-73. Delete the tribe Pup., in MRR 2.490 and the Index, 560. He may be identified as a son of no. 19, Cos. 162, and a brother of no. 20, Cos. 122. See MRR 1.496-497, note 1. On the date, see above, M.' Aquillius (10)\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6863> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6863" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Senator in 129 (S. C. de Agro Pergameno). Identified by Cichorius with L. Domitius Ahenobarbus, Cos. 94 (Untersuch. Lucil. 3f.; followed by Magie, Roman Rule in Asia Minor 2.1055, note 25), but as the S. C. de Agro Pergameno should probably be dated in 129 Domitius is more probably a member of the previous generation (see above, 133, note 1)." .
